  "series": "2000 Issue \"Birds\"",
  "comments": "<p>On the obverse upper left there is a brown panel with a butterfly and a 5 that appears or disappears with a tilt of the note:</p><p><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6794dc2f99fad.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6794dc2f99fad.jpg\"></a> &nbsp;<a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6794dc3caaeb8.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6794dc3caaeb8.jpg\"></a></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>The note has a solid security strip windowed into six pieces on the reverse. Under backlight the whole strip can be seen and read. It has “CBVS 5” repeated on it:</p><p><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/6794dc9132fac.jpg\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/6794dc9132fac.jpg\"></a></p><p>© Brandon Bertolli</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p>UV activity: Value in box, butterflies, bat wings, and trees fluoresce green.<br><a href=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/64ece69214d1b.png\"><img src=\"https://en.numista.com/catalogue/images/miniatures/64ece69214d1b.png\" alt=\"\"></a><br>© gyoschak<br><br>P#146, signature Henk Goedschalk - President of the Central Bank of Suriname from January 1985 until January 1994; and from January 1997 until August 2000.</p>",
